form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->, {{t+check|kmr|seh|alt=seh kirin}} <!-- was \"{{tt+|kmr|seh|alt=seh kirin}}\" - assumed inflected form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->, {{t+check|kmr|fekirin}}, {{t+check|kmr|hêv|alt=hêv kirin}} <!-- was \"{{tt+|kmr|hêv|alt=hêv kirin}}\" - assumed inflected form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->, {{t+check|kmr|mêze|alt=mêze kirin}} <!-- was \"{{tt+|kmr|mêze|alt=mêze kirin}}\" - assumed inflected form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:Kephir/gadgets/xte#Translation_fixing]] -->, {{t+check|kmr|mêzandin}}, {{t+check|kmr|mêzîn}}\n* Latin: {{t-check|la|spectare}}\n* Occitan: {{t+check|oc|agachar}}\n* Persian: {{t+check|fa|دیدَن|tr=didan}}, {{t+check|fa|بین|tr=bin}}\n* Swahili: {{t+check|sw|kuangalia}}\n* Tagalog: {{t-check|tl|tumingin}}, {{t-check|tl|tingnan}}, {{t-check|tl|sulyapan}}, {{t-check|tl|masdan}}, {{t-check|tl|punahin}}, {{t-check|tl|pansinin}}, {{t-check|tl|etc.}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|nang-nak}}, {{t-check|wyi|nganga}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# [[pay attention|Pay attention]].\n#: {{ux|en|'''Look''', I'm going to explain what to do, so you have to listen closely.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=w:Cynthia Harrod-Eagles|chapter=Not Buried But In Turd|title=Gone Tomorrow|location=London|publisher=w:Little, Brown and Company|page=203|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/gonetomorrow0000harr_w9u5/page/203/mode/1up|isbn=0 316 85741 6|passage=‘'''Look''',’ he began, and she flapped a hand to stop him. ‘For God’s sake don’t say anything that starts with “'''look'''”. Sentences like that lead anywhere and they’re always fatal.’}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n{{col|en|see|so|well|hey|look at me|listen|listen up}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|interjection to attract attention}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|виж}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|katsos}}, {{tt|fi|katsokaas}} {{qualifier|plural}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|écoute}}, {{tt+|fr|écoutez|p}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|cata}} {{qualifier|archaic}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt|hu|nézze}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|kas}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|guarda qui!}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|[[보다|봐]][[보다|-봐]]}}, {{t|ko|[[듣다|들어]][[보다|-봐]]}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|age}}, {{tt+|la|agite}} (plural)\n* Māori: {{tt|mi|rē}}, {{t|mi|ināia}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|बघ}} {{qualifier|informal singular}}, {{t|mr|बघा}} {{qualifier|informal plural, formal}}\n* Nǀuu: {{t|ngh|nǀaa}}, {{t|ngh|nǀii}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|słuchaj}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|ia}}, {{t|ro|uite}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|смотри́}} {{qualifier|informal singular}}, {{tt+|ru|смотри́те}} {{qualifier|informal plural|formal}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|mirar}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|titta}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# The [[action]] of looking; an [[attempt]] to [[see]].\n#: {{ux|en|Let’s have a '''look''' under the hood of the car.}}\n# {{lb|en|often plural}} Physical [[appearance]], [[visual]] [[impression]].\n#: {{ux|en|She got her mother’s '''looks'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|I don’t like the '''look''' of the new design.}}\n#* {{RQ:Marshall Squire's Daughter|I\n|passage=He tried to persuade Cicely to stay away from the ball-room for a fourth dance. {{...}} But she said she must go back, and when they joined the crowd again her partner was haled off with a frightened '''look''' to the royal circle, {{...}}}}\n# A [[facial]] [[expression]].\n#: {{ux|en|He gave me a dirty '''look'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|If '''looks''' could kill ...}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|man look|freelook|hindlook|look-back| look dev|look development\n|afterlook|forelook|forthlook|have a look|if looks could kill|inlook|lookist|mislook\n|new-look|onlook|outlook|overlook|relook|underlook|a good look|black look|dirty look|doggy dinner bowl look|look and feel|lookbook|look-in|old-fashioned look|take a look|lookdown|lookful|lookism|lookless|lookoff|looksome|looky-loo|mouselook|wetlook\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|nl|look|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|look|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ro|look|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ru|лук|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|es|look|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|look|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-see|action of looking|glance}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|نَظْرَة|f}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|نَظْرَة|f|tr=naẓra}}, {{tt|acw|شوفة|f|tr=šōfa}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|so}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|по́гляд}}, {{tt|be|по́зірк|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|по́глед|m}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|ullada|f}}, {{tt+|ca|cop d'ull|m}}, {{tt+|ca|mirada|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|目光|tr=mùguāng}}, {{tt+|cmn|一見|tr=yījiàn}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pohled}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|blik|m}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|katsominen}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|regard|m}}\n* Galician: {{tt|gl|ollada|f}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|ყურება}}, {{tt|ka|ცქერა}}, {{tt|ka|ჭვრეტა}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Blick|m}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|βλέμμα|n}}, {{tt+|el|ματιά|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|βλέμμα|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מבט|m|tr=mabát}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|pillantás}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|occhiata|f}}, {{tt+|it|sguardo|m}}, {{tt+|it|aspetto|m}} {{qualifier|literary}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|一見|tr=いっけん, ikken}}, {{tt+|ja|一目|tr=いちもく, ichimoku, ひと​め, hitome}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|일견(一見)}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|поглед|m}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt|nb|blikk|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|blikk|n}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|pogląd|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|olhada|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|privire|f}}, {{t+|ro|vedere|f}}\n* Romansh: {{tt|rm|egliada|f}} {{qualifier|Rumantsch Grischun|Sursilvan}}, {{tt|rm|iglieada|f}} {{qualifier|Sutsilvan}}, {{tt|rm|igleida}} {{qualifier|Surmiran}}, {{tt|rm|öglieda|f}} {{qualifier|Puter}}, {{tt|rm|sguard|m}} {{qualifier|Puter|Vallader}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|взгляд|m}}\n* Scots: {{tt|sco|leuk}}, {{tt|sco|luke}}, {{tt|sco|luik}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|sùil|f}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt+|scn|taliata|f}}, {{tt+|scn|ucchiata|f}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|pohľad|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|vistazo|m}}, {{t+|es|ojeada|f}}, {{t+|es|mirada|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|angalia}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|blick|c}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|చూపు}}\n* Tocharian B: {{tt|txb|pilko}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|bakma}}, {{tt+|tr|bakış}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{tt|ota|باقم|tr=bakım}}, {{tt|ota|نگاه|tr=nigâh}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|по́гляд|m}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|קוק}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|bıvin}}, {{tt|zza|bıase}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|physical appearance}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|kyk}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|مَرْأىً|m}}, {{tt+|ar|مَرْآة|f}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|արտաքին}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|vidzutã|f}}, {{tt|rup|videalã|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|görünüş}}, {{tt+|az|görkəm}}, {{tt|az|zahiri görünüş}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt+|be|вы́гляд|m}}, {{tt|be|зне́шнасць|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|вид|m}}, {{tt+|bg|въ́ншност|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|樣子|tr=yàngzi}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|vzhled|m}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|uitzicht|n}}, {{qualifier|about a person}} {{tt+|nl|look|m}}, {{tt+|nl|uiterlijk|n}}, {{tt+|nl|stijl|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt|eo|aspekto}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|ulkonäkö}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|air|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|გარეგნობა}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Aussehen|n}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|όψη|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{tt|grc|ἰδέα|f}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מראה|m|tr=mar`é}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|kinézet}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|aspetto|m}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|様子|tr=ようす, yōsu}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|모양(模樣)}}, {{tt|ko|외형(外形)}}, {{tt+|ko|외관(外觀)}}\n* Kumyk: {{tt|kum|кюц}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|изглед|m}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|रुप|n}}\n* Norwegian: {{tt+|no|utseende|n}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|wygląd|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|aspecto|m}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|aspect|n}}, {{tt+|ro|înfățișare|f}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|вид|m}}, {{tt+|ru|вне́шность|f}}\n* Scots: {{tt|sco|leuk}}, {{tt|sco|luke}}, {{tt|sco|luik}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|coltas|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|изглед|m}}\n*: Latin: {{tt|sh|izgled|m}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt+|scn|aspettu|m}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|vzhľad|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|aspecto|m}}, {{t+|es|apariencia|f}}, {{t+|es|imagen|f}}, {{t+|es|facha|f}}, {{t|es|''look''|m}}, {{t+|es|viso|m}}, {{t+|es|pinta|f}}, {{t+|es|aire|m}}, {{t+|es|porte|m}}, {{t+|es|prestancia|f}}, {{t+|es|fisionomía|f}}, {{t+|es|fisonomía|f}}, {{t+|es|facies|f}}, {{t+|es|estampa|f}}, {{t+|es|ver|m}}, {{t+|es|pergeño|m}}, {{t+|es|pergenio|m}}, {{t+|es|cariz|m}} {{qualifier|of the atmosphere}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|angalia}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|utseende|n}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|หน้าตา}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|görünüş}}, {{tt+|tr|görünüm}}, {{tt+|tr|görüntü}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|نمایش|tr=nümayiş}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|ви́гляд|m}}, {{tt|uk|зо́внішність|f}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|bıase}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|facial expression}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|по́гляд|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|израже́ние|n}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|pohled|m}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|blik|m}}\n* Estonian: {{tt|et|pilk}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|ilme}}, {{tt+|fi|katse}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|regard|m}}, {{tt+|fr|mine|f}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Fratze|f}}, {{tt+|de|Blick|m}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|מבט|m|tr=mabát}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|tekintet}}, {{tt+|hu|pillantás}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|dreach|m}}\n* Italian: {{tt|it|occhiataccia|f}}, {{tt+|it|ghigno|m}}, {{tt+|it|espressione|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|поглед|m}}\n* Norman: {{tt|nrf|èrgard|m}} {{qualifier|Jersey}}\n* Norwegian: {{tt+|no|uttrykk|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|olhar|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|взгляд|m}}\n* Scots: {{tt|sco|leuk}}, {{tt|sco|luke}}, {{tt|sco|luik}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|fiamh|m}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|pogled|m}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|mirada|f}}, {{t+|es|expresión|f}}, {{t+|es|fisonomía|f}}, {{t+|es|fisionomía|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|angalia}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|blick|c}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|หน้าตา}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|bakış}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|по́гляд|m}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|bıweyn}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|cinéma du look}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=kloo|kolo|kool}}\n\n{{C|en|Appearance|Communication}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|yue|en|look}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{zh-pron\n|c=luk1\n|cat=n\n}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|zh|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} {{l|en|look}}; [[physical]] [[appearance]]; [[visual]] [[impression]]; [[style]]; [[outfit]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:yue:ELHKC}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|nl|dum|look}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|*lōc}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*laukaz}}. Compare {{cog|nds|look}}, {{m|nds|Look}}, {{cog|de|Lauch}}, {{cog|en|leek}}, {{cog|da|løg}}, {{cog|sv|lök}}. More at {{m|en|leek}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|nl|/loːk/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-look1.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|look}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|oːk|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|nl|Look}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|n,m|-en|+}}\n\n# {{C|nl|Alliums}} any [[plant]] of the [[genus]] {{taxfmt|Allium|genus}}; [[leek]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|lookachtig\n|lookallergie\n|lookbed\n|lookgeur\n|looksaus\n|looksmaak\n|looksoep\n|lookstank\n|lookworst\n}}\n{{col|nl|title=species\n|beerlook\n|bieslook <t:chives>\n|berglook <t:keeled garlic>\n|daklook <t:common houseleek, Sempervivum tectorum>\n|daslook <t:bear leek>\n|eslook <t:shallot>\n|huislook <t:houseleek, sempervivum>\n|knoflook <t:garlic>\n|kraailook <t:crow garlic>\n|lookprei\n|look-zonder-look\n|moeslook <t:field garlic>\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|nl|/loːk/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-look1.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|look}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|oːk|s=1}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|nl|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|nl|luiken||s|past|ind}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|look}}. {{doublet|nl|loekoe}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|nl|/luk/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-look.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|look}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|uk|s=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-s|-}}\n\n# a {{l|en|look}}, (clothing) style, [[appearance]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|nl|horrorlook}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\nRelated to [[luiken]], cognate with English [[lock]].\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-en|+}}\n\n# a [[gap]], space between [[barrel]]s or between the strings in [[rope]]\n# a [[section]], [[division]] {{q|archaic}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|nl|kool}}\n\n{{cln|nl|heteronyms}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:look}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|look}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|louk}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-look.ogg}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-DenisdeShawi-look.wav|a=<<Canada>> (<<Shawinigan>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# a [[style]]; [[appearance]]; {{l|en|look}}\n#: {{uxi|fr|Je trouve que son nouveau '''look''' ne lui va pas du tout.|t=I think his new '''look''' doesn't suit him at all.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|relooker}}\n* {{l|fr|relooking}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|look}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA|br=lúqui|pt=lúki^}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|#s}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|informal}} {{l|en|look}}; [[outfit]], [[style]] {{gloss|a set of clothing with accessories}}\n#: {{syn|pt|visual}}\n#: {{uxi|pt|Amei seu '''look'''.|I love your '''outfit'''.}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{C|pt|Clothing}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|ro|en|look}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|n|lookuri}}\n\n# {{l|en|look}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-n-uri}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|look}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|luk}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|es|informal}} a {{l|en|look}}; [[style]], [[appearance]]\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n==Tagalog==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|tl|looc||obsolete|Abecedario}}\n* {{alt|tl|luok||nonstandard}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|tl|poz-pro|*luquk||bay}}. Compare {{cog|ilo|luek}}, {{cog|pam|lauk}}, {{cog|ceb|luok}}, {{cog|tsg|luuk}}, and {{cog|ms|teluk}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{tl-pr|lo7ók|lo7ok<qq:obsolete><hmp:Looc>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{tl-noun|loók|b=+}}\n\n# {{lb|tl|geography}} [[bay]] {{gl|body of water}}\n#: {{syn|tl|baiya}}\n#: {{uxi|tl|'''Look''' ng Maynila|Manila '''Bay'''}}\n# [[middle]] [[part]] of a [[bay]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|tl|kalookan|Kalookan}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col3|tl|golpo|laot}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:Pambansang Diksiyonaryo}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|tl|a=kloo|loko}}\n\n{{C|tl|Bodies of water}}"}}